t%3B%20event%20in%20San%20Francisco%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6879969485e81483682e3f2f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221969%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EStackBlitz%20CEO%20Eric%20Simons%20talks%20during%20the%20startup's%20%26quot%3Bhackathon%26quot%3B%20event%20in%20San%20Francisco%3Cp%3EAlistair%20Barr%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESimons%20thinks%20Anthropic%20had%20its%20existing%20models%20write%20code%20and%20deploy%20it.%20Then%2C%20the%20company%20evaluated%20all%20the%20deployed%20code%2C%20through%20a%20combination%C2%A0human%20expertise%20and%20automated%20AI%20analysis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20software%20coding%2C%20it's%20relatively%20easy%20to%20evaluate%20good%20versus%20bad%20outputs.%20That's%20because%20the%20code%20either%20works%2C%20or%20it%20doesn't%2C%20when%20deployed.%20This%20creates%20clear%20YES%20and%20NO%20signals%20that%20are%20really%20valuable%20for%20training%20and%20fine-tuning%20new%20AI%20models%2C%20he%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnthropic%20took%20these%20signals%20and%20funneled%20them%20into%20the%20training%20data%20and%20development%20process%20for%20the%20new%20Sonnet%20AI%20models.%20This%20reinforcement-learning%20strategy%20produced%20AI%20models%20that%20were%20much%20better%20at%20coding%2C%20according%20to%20Simons%2C%20who%20was%20equally%20blown%20away%20by%20Sonnet%203.5's%20abilities%20in%20the%20summer%20of%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a3d9dc1e-bb65-4cab-8536-251d7c43e3a9%5C%22%3EHuman%20versus%20AI%20evaluations%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221369%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ben%20Mann%2C%20cofounder%20of%20Anthropic%2C%20talks%20on%20the%20No%20Priors%20podcast%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F687ac498f748d8c055f5eb10%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221045%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBen%20Mann%2C%20cofounder%20of%20Anthropic%2C%20talks%20on%20the%20No%20Priors%20podcast%3Cp%3ENo%20Priors%2FYouTube%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAnthropic%20cofounder%20Ben%20Mann%20appeared%20on%20a%20podcast%20recently%20and%20seemed%20to%20revel%20in%20the%20idea%20that%20the%20rest%20of%20Silicon%20Valley%20still%20hadn't%20caught%20up%20with%20his%20startup's%20AI%20coding%20abilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOther%20companies%20have%20had%2C%20like%2C%20code%20reds%20for%20trying%20to%20catch%20up%20in%20coding%20capabilities%20for%20quite%20a%20while%20and%20have%20not%20been%20able%20to%20do%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BHonestly%2C%20I'm%20kind%20of%20surprised%20that%20they%20weren't%20able%20to%20catch%20up%2C%20but%20I'll%20take%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20when%20pushed%20for%20answers%2C%20he%20explained%20some%20of%20the%20keys%20to%20Anthropic's%20success%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMann%20built%20Anthropic's%20human%20feedback%20data%20system%20in%202021.%20Back%20then%2C%20it%20was%20relatively%20easy%20for%20humans%20to%20evaluate%20signals%2C%20such%20as%20whether%20model%20output%20A%20was%20better%20than%20B%2C%20and%20feed%20that%20back%20into%20the%20AI%20development%20process%20via%20a%20popular%20technique%20known%20as%20Reinforcement%20Learning%20from%20Human%20Feedback%2C%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-memo-meta-scale-ai-investment-mark-zuckerberg-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ERLHF%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20we've%20trained%20the%20models%20more%20and%20scaled%20up%20a%20lot%2C%20it's%20become%20harder%20to%20find%20humans%20with%20enough%20expertise%20to%20meaningfully%20contribute%20to%20these%20feedback%20comparisons%2C%26quot%3B%20Mann%20explained%20on%20the%20No%20Priors%20podcast.%20%26quot%3BFor%20coding%2C%20somebody%20who%20isn't%20already%20an%20expert%20software%20engineer%20would%20probably%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20trouble%20judging%20whether%20one%20thing%20or%20another%20was%20better.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20Anthropic%20pioneered%20a%20new%20approach%20called%20Reinforcement%20Learning%20from%20AI%20Feedback%2C%20or%20RLAIF.%20Instead%20of%20humans%20evaluating%20AI%20model%20outputs%2C%20other%20models%20would%20do%20the%20analysis.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20make%20this%20more-automated%20technique%20work%2C%20Anthropic%20wrote%20a%20series%20of%20principals%20in%20English%20for%20its%20models%20to%20adhere%20to.%20The%20startup%20called%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.anthropic.com%2Fresearch%2Fconstitutional-ai-harmlessness-from-ai-feedback%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EConstitutional%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20process%20is%20very%20simple%2C%26quot%3B%20Mann%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20just%20take%20a%20random%20prompt%20like%20'How%20should%20I%20think%20about%20my%20taxes%3F'%20and%20then%20you%20have%20the%20model%20write%20a%20response.%20Then%20you%20have%20the%20model%20criticize%20its%20own%20response%20with%20respect%20to%20one%20of%20the%20principles%2C%20and%20if%20it%20didn't%20comply%20with%20the%20principle%2C%20then%20you%20have%20the%20model%20correct%20its%20response.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20coding%2C%20you%20can%20give%20the%20AI%20models%20principles%20such%20as%20%26quot%3BDid%20it%20actually%20serve%20the%20final%20answer%3F%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BDid%20it%20do%20a%20bunch%20of%20stuff%20that%20the%20person%20didn't%20ask%20for%3F%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BDoes%20this%20code%20look%20maintainable%3F%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BAre%20the%20comments%20useful%20and%20interesting%3F%26quot%3B%20Mann%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22840f9932-804a-47cc-87a0-68fa021ba345%5C%22%3EDr.%20Mann's%20empirical%20method%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-memo-ai-winners-startups-vibe-coding-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EElad%20Gil%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20top%20AI%20investor%20and%20No%20Priors%20host%2C%20concurred%2C%20saying%20the%20clear%20signals%20from%20deploying%20code%20and%20seeing%20it%20if%20works%2C%20makes%20this%20process%20fruitful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20coding%2C%20you%20actually%20have%20like%20a%20direct%20output%20that%20you%20can%20measure%3A%20You%20can%20run%20the%20code%2C%20you%20can%20test%20the%20code%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20sort%20of%20a%20baked-in%20utility%20function%20you%20can%20optimize%20against.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMann%20cited%20an%20example%20from%20his%20father%2C%20who%20was%20a%20physician.%20One%20day%2C%20a%20patient%20came%20in%20with%20a%20skin%20condition%20on%20his%20face%2C%20and%20Dr.%20Mann%20couldn't%20find%20what%20the%20problem%20was.%20So%2C%20he%20divided%20the%20patient's%20face%20into%20sections%20and%20applied%20different%20treatments.%20One%20area%20cleared%20up%2C%20revealing%20the%20answer%20empirically.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSometimes%20you%20just%20won't%20know%20and%20you%20have%20to%20try%20stuff%20%E2%80%94%20and%20with%20code%20that's%20easy%20because%20we%20can%20just%20do%20it%20in%20a%20loop%2C%26quot%3B%20Anthropic's%20Mann%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2228b96732-28b6-4f95-94db-fa92b48adf18%5C%22%3EConstitutional%20AI%20and%20beyond%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dianne%20Penn%2C%20Head%20of%20Product%20Management%2C%20Research%20and%20Frontiers%2C%20at%20Anthropic%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F687ac63685e81483682e516d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDianne%20Penn%2C%20Head%20of%20Product%20Management%2C%20Research%20and%20Frontiers%2C%20at%20Anthropic%3Cp%3EEvan-Marie%20Petit%20Photography%2FAnthropic%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20with%20BI%2C%20Anthropic's%20Penn%20described%20other%20ingredients%20that%20went%20into%20making%20the%20startup's%20models%20so%20good%20at%20coding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20the%20description%20from%20Simons%2C%20the%20StackBlitz%20CEO%2C%20was%C2%A0%26quot%3Bgenerally%20true%2C%26quot%3B%20while%20noting%20that%20Anthropic's%20coding%20breakthrough%20was%20the%20result%20of%20a%20multiyear%20effort%20involving%20many%20researchers%20and%20lots%20of%20ideas%20and%20techniques.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20fundamentally%20made%20it%20good%20at%20writing%20code%2C%20or%20being%20able%20to%20figure%20out%20what%20good%20code%20looks%20like%2C%20through%20what%20you%20can%20consider%20as%20trial%20and%20iterations%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20giving%20the%20model%20different%20questions%20and%20allowing%20it%20to%20figure%20out%20what%20the%20right%20answer%20is%20on%20a%20coding%20problem.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20about%20the%20role%20of%20Constitutional%20AI%2C%20Penn%20said%20she%20couldn't%20share%C2%A0too%20much%20detail%20on%20the%20exact%20techniques%2C%20but%20said%20%26quot%3Bit's%20definitely%20in%20the%20models.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224330261f-9a6f-4f4c-b5af-a2b49faa3f8a%5C%22%3EUsing%20tools%20with%20no%20hands%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnthropic%20also%20trained%20Sonnet%203.5%20to%20be%20much%20better%20at%20using%20tools%2C%20a%20key%20focus%20that%20has%20begun%20to%20turn%20AI%20models%20from%20chatbots%20into%20more%20general-purpose%20agents%20%E2%80%94%20what%20the%20startup%20calls%C2%A0%26quot%3Bvirtual%20collaborators.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20don't%20have%20hands%2C%26quot%3B%20Penn%20said%2C%20so%20instead%2C%20Anthropic's%20models%20were%20trained%20to%20write%20code%20themselves%20to%20access%20digital%20tools.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20she%20said%20that%20if%20an%20Anthropic%20model%20is%20asked%20for%20weather%20information%20or%20stock%20prices%2C%20it%20can%20write%C2%A0software%20to%20tap%20into%20an%20application%20programming%20interface%2C%20or%20API%2C%20a%20common%20way%20for%20apps%20to%20access%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22515db824-0b52-4960-9913-c4ba2a410480%5C%22%3EFollowing%20instructions%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20software%20coding%20projects%20get%20really%20big%2C%20you%20can't%20knock%20out%20the%20work%20in%20a%20few%20minutes.%20The%20more%20complex%20tasks%20take%20days%2C%20weeks%2C%20or%20longer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20models%20have%20been%20incapable%20of%20sticking%20with%20long-term%20jobs%20like%20these.%20But%20Anthropic%20invested%20heavily%20in%20making%20Sonnet%203.5%20and%20later%20models%20much%20better%20at%20following%20human%20instructions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20way%2C%20if%20the%20model%20gets%20stumped%20on%20a%20long%20coding%20problem%2C%20it%20can%20take%20guidance%20from%20developers%20to%20keep%20going%20%E2%80%94%20essentially%20listening%20better%20to%20understand%20the%20intent%20of%20its%20human%20colleagues%2C%20Penn%20explained.%20(Hey%2C%20we%20can%20all%20get%20better%20at%20that).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225c253ccd-4ce3-4f2b-9d9e-f9d1d10eeda5%5C%22%3EKnowing%20what%20to%20remember%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Anthropic%20CEO%20Dario%20Amodei%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68715dc8f748d8c055f57d32%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22802%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAnthropic%20CEO%20Dario%20Amodei%20talking%20onstage%20with%20Chief%20Product%20Officer%20Mike%20Krieger%20(left).%3Cp%3EAnthropic%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20the%20best%20human%20software%20developers%20can't%20keep%20everything%20related%20to%20a%20coding%20project%20in%20their%20brains.%20GitHub%20repositories%2C%20holding%20code%2C%20images%2C%20documentation%2C%20and%20revision%20histories%2C%20can%20be%20massive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20Anthropic%20trained%20is%20AI%20models%20to%20create%20a%20kind%20of%20scratch%20pad%20where%20it%20jots%20down%20notes%20in%20an%20external%20file%20system%20as%20it's%20exploring%20things%20like%20a%20code%20base.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20train%20it%20to%20use%20that%20tool%20very%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20Penn%20said%20(while%20I%20frantically%20scribbled%20notes%20on%20my%20own%20reporting%20pad).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20key%20here%20is%20that%20Anthropic's%20models%20were%20trained%20to%20remember%20more%20of%20the%20salient%20details%20of%20coding%20projects%2C%20and%20ignore%20the%20less%20important%20stuff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20useful%20to%20say%2C%20'Dianne%20is%20wearing%20a%20colored%20shirt%20in%20this%20conversation%2C%20and%20Alistair%20is%20wearing%20a%20green%20shirt%2C'%26quot%3B%20Penn%20said%2C%20describing%20the%20BI%20interview%20taking%20place%20at%20that%20moment.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20more%20important%20to%20note%20that%20we%20talked%20about%20coding%20and%20how%20Anthropic%20focused%20on%20coding%20quality.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20better%20use%20of%20memory%20means%20that%20Anthropic%20models%20can%20suggest%20multiple%20code%20changes%20over%20the%20course%20of%20an%20entire%20project%2C%20something%20that%20other%20AI%20models%20aren't%20as%20good%20at.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20it's%20not%20trained%20well%2C%20it%20could%20scribble%20the%20wrong%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20Penn%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20gotten%20really%20good%20at%20those%20things.%20So%20it%20actually%20does%20not%20just%20mean%20in%20the%20short%20term%20that%20it%20can%20write%20good%20code%2C%20but%20it%20remembers%20to%20write%20data%20so%20that%20it%20might%20make%20a%20second%20or%20third%20change%20that%20another%20AI%20model%20might%20not%20know%2C%20because%20the%20quality%20of%20its%20notes%2C%20plus%20the%20quality%20of%20its%20core%20intelligence%2C%20are%20better.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2288f9be05-957e-423f-8b8d-1e3d26df9788%5C%22%3EClaude%20Code%20and%20terminal%20data%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20while%2C%20in%20around%202022%2C%20it%20looked%20like%20AI%20progress%20was%20happening%20automatically%2C%20through%20more%20data%2C%20more%20GPUs%2C%20and%20bigger%20training%20runs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20reality%20is%20that%20there%20are%20very%20discrete%20breakthroughs%2C%20and%20very%20discrete%20ideas%20that%20lead%20to%20these%20breakthroughs%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Armando%20Solar-Lezama%2C%20a%20distinguished%20professor%20of%20computing%20at%20MIT.%20%26quot%3BIt%20takes%20researchers%2C%20and%20investment%20in%20research%2C%20to%20produce%20the%20next%20idea%20that%20leads%20to%20the%20next%20breakthrough.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20how%20Anthropic's%20hard-won%20coding%20lead%20happened.%20But%20access%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwindsurf-google-cognition-acquisition-ai-coding-developer-data-ide-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edetailed%2C%20granular%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20how%20human%20developers%20write%20software%20is%20crucial%20to%20stay%20ahead%20in%20this%20part%20of%20the%20AI%20race%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Filev%20has%20a%20theory%20related%20to%20this.%20He's%20CEO%20of%20Zencoder%2C%20another%20AI%20coding%20service%20that%20uses%20Anthropic's%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225760%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Andrew%20Filev%20CEO%20of%20Zencoder%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5efdf5de2618b92fe72d9168%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223840%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAndrew%20Filev%2C%20CEO%20of%20Zencoder%3Cp%3EFilev%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFilev%20thinks%20that%20data%20from%20computer%20terminal%20use%20is%20key%20to%20training%20AI%20models%20to%20be%20good%20at%20coding.%20A%20terminal%20is%20a%20text-based%20interface%20that%20lets%20developers%20send%20instructions%20to%20a%20computer's%20operating%20system%20or%20software.%20They%20type%20in%20information%20via%20a%C2%A0%26quot%3Bcommand%20line%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20hopefully%20get%20outputs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLarge%20language%20models%20are%20great%20with%20text%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me%20in%20a%20recent%20interview%20about%20Anthropic.%20%26quot%3BThe%20computer%20terminal%2C%20where%20you%20keep%20commands%2C%20is%20basically%20text%2C%20too.%20So%20at%20some%20point%2C%20people%20realized%20that%20they%20should%20just%20give%20that%20data%20to%20their%20AI%20model%2C%20and%20it%20can%20do%20amazing%20things%20%E2%80%94%20things%20which%20previously%20had%20never%20worked.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20late%20May%2C%20Anthropic%20rolled%20out%20Claude%20Code%2C%20a%20command%20line%20tool%20for%20AI%20coding%20that%20works%20with%20developers'%20existing%20terminals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuddenly%2C%20Anthropic%20is%20now%20competing%20against%20its%20main%20customers%20%E2%80%94%20all%20those%20other%20AI%20coding%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20move%20also%20created%20a%20direct%20relationship%20between%20Anthropic%20and%20developers%2C%20giving%20the%20AI%20lab%20access%20to%20a%20richer%20source%20of%20data%20on%20how%20expert%20humans%20write%20software.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20amount%20and%20the%20speed%20that%20we%20learn%20is%20much%20less%20if%20we%20don't%20have%20a%20direct%20relationship%20with%20our%20coding%20users%2C%26quot%3B%20Anthropic's%20Mann%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20launching%20Claude%20Code%20was%20really%20essential%20for%20us%20to%20get%20a%20better%20sense%20of%20what%20do%20people%20need%2C%20how%20do%20we%20make%20the%20models%20better%2C%20and%20how%20do%20we%20advance%20the%20state-of-the-art%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20theory%2C%20this%20granular%20information%20could%20be%20used%20to%20help%20train%20and%20fine-tune%20Anthropic's%20next%20models%2C%20potentially%20giving%20the%20startup%20a%20data%20edge%20that%20might%20preserve%20its%20AI%20coding%20lead%20even%20longer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCould%20I%20do%20this%20without%20Anthropic's%20latest%20models%3F%20No%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Sou