Karonda%20has%20spread%20joy%20across%20the%20country%2C%20and%20the%20best%20part%3F%20It%20is%20easily%20grown%20at%20home.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%E2%80%99s%20your%20guide%20to%20cultivating%20this%20hardy%2C%20drought-tolerant%20fruit%20during%20the%20monsoon%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E1.%20Choosing%20your%20propagation%20method%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKaronda%20can%20be%20grown%20from%20seeds%2C%20cuttings%2C%20or%20air%20layering.%20During%20monsoon%2C%20both%20cuttings%20and%20air%20layering%20can%20be%20successful.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20cuttings%2C%20take%20semi-hardwood%20cuttings%20(about%2025-30%20cm%20long).%20Whereas%20air%20layering%20method%20involves%20inducing%20roots%20to%20form%20on%20a%20branch%20while%20it%E2%80%99s%20still%20attached%20to%20the%20parent%20plant.%20The%20rooted%20air%20layers%20are%20ready%20for%20transplanting%20after%20about%20three%20and%20a%20half%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20you%E2%80%99re%20propagating%20from%20seeds%2C%20sow%20them%20in%20August%20or%20September%20for%20better%20germination%20and%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E2.%20Preparing%20the%20soil%20and%20planting%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F454949%2Fmonsoon-kitchen-garden-guide-grow-your-vegetables-and-herbs-monsoon-season-temperature-soil%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DStep%252Dby%252Dstep%2520guide%2520to%2Cgood%2520air%2520circulation%2520around%2520plants.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emonsoon%20season%20%3C%2Fa%3Eis%20a%20good%20time%20for%20planting.%20Choose%20a%20spot%20that%20receives%20plenty%20of%20sunlight%2C%20and%20ensure%20the%20soil%20is%20well-drained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F20